description:
Next, we continue the discovery of Martin Luther's life. After leaving the monastery, he went on to teach at the University of Wittenberg. He then continued to successfully preach, after encouragement from his peers. A dispute arose between local covents, which lead Luther to embark on a trip that would change his life forever. Being called to go to Rome, on what he thought would be a pilgrimage, changed his life - but for different reasons than he anticipated.

To find out more information about Martin Luther read our extended article.
